<section class="p-6 bg-white shadow rounded-md mb-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Earnings</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    The Earnings page is where creators track all revenue generated from their published articles.
    It provides a detailed breakdown of income sources and trends, helping creators optimize their content for maximum revenue.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Sections Included:</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Total Earnings:</strong> Overview of all revenue earned to date.</li>
    <li><strong>Article-wise Earnings:</strong> Revenue breakdown for each published article.</li>
    <li><strong>Revenue Sources:</strong> Tracks income from ads, views, shares, and other monetization methods.</li>
    <li><strong>Graphs & Trends:</strong> Visual chart of earnings over time (weekly/monthly).</li>
    <li><strong>Pending Payments:</strong> Displays revenue awaiting processing or release.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">User Process on Earnings Page:</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
    <li>Login and navigate to Earnings page.</li>
    <li>View Total Earnings for a quick overview of income.</li>
    <li>Check article-wise earnings to see which content performs best financially.</li>
    <li>Analyze revenue trends via graphs to track growth.</li>
    <li>Note pending payments and prepare for withdrawals.</li>
    <li>Decide which articles to focus on for higher revenue in the future.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Purpose of This Page:</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
    The Earnings page allows creators to understand their financial performance, identify
    profitable content, and make informed decisions about future articles and monetization strategies.
  </p>
</section>
